# DocBot v3 — Implementation Plan

## Background

The existing `doc_automation_v2` repository is a working but architecturally fragile documentation automation pipeline. This plan transforms it into the world-class v3 platform described in the spec, fixing all W1–W30 defects while keeping the pipeline runnable after every phase.

The repo currently sits flat (all `.py` files at root), with providers, manual_builder, ui, styles, content, and templates as subdirectories.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Provider reality:** The only working provider is `ollama` (Ollama cloud endpoint, model `gpt-oss:120b`, key via `OLLAMA_API_KEY`). This model is TEXT-ONLY. Vision is implemented but dormant; the v3 prompt phrases vision conditionally. All generation produces correct output via the text path. This is by spec.

> [!WARNING]
> **Git history:** The plan calls for `git rm -r --cached` on `.env`, `venv/`, `__pycache__/`, `sessions/`, and `Final_Manuals/`. This removes them from tracking but does NOT delete local files. The previously committed `OLLAMA_API_KEY` must be rotated by the owner — a note goes in the README (the spec explicitly requires this).

> [!WARNING]
> **File reorganization:** The plan restructures directories significantly (`content/` + `styles/` → `clients/`, flat root `.py` files → `docbot/` package, `providers/prompts/` → `prompts/v3/`). Import shims are left until Phase 7 so the app stays runnable at each phase boundary. This means `labeler.py`, `detect_regions.py`, etc. will temporarily re-export from their new homes.

> [!CAUTION]
> **Review UI rewrite (Phase 7):** `review_ui.py` (33 KB) is completely rewritten. The spec mandates this. Any session data the writer has already reviewed in the old UI will be preserved via `session.json`/`migrate_legacy`. Old review state (the `_final.json` per screen) is migrated.

