## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q1 — `sessions/` data:** There are existing sessions in `sessions/`. Should `migrate_legacy` run automatically on startup (reading old `screen_N_*.json` files into `session.json`) or only when the writer explicitly opens an old session in the review UI? The plan assumes **automatic migration on session open**.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q2 — Module numbering for NCD:** The spec's continuous numbering example (2 Login, 3 Dashboard, 4.4.1 Cooperatives…) implies that *some* modules are a single screen (numbered at top level) and others contain multiple screens (numbered as subsections). The rule proposed: "if the module has exactly one screen, that screen IS the level-1 section." Is this correct for NCD, or should level-1 always be the module and screens always be level-2?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q3 — Capture mode default:** The spec says default `mode: viewport`. The existing code always uses `full_page=True`. Switching the default will change the look of screenshots for existing sessions. Should existing sessions keep their screenshots untouched (only new captures use viewport mode), or should the default be `full_page` for backward compat and writers opt in to viewport?

