## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests (Phase 8)
```
pytest tests/ -v --no-header
```
All tests use `FakeProvider` — no network, no Playwright.

### Phase Boundary Checks
Each phase ends by running:
```
python -m docbot.ui.launcher   # must open without error
```

### Manual Verification (Phases 5, 6)
- Build a session under client `ncd` → open docx in Word:
  - Revision history is page 1
  - Sections numbered 1/2/3 continuously
  - Field bullets in "Name – description" form
  - Banner header on every page
  - A crop image inline in a step
  - Update Field in Word populates TOC AND Table of Figures correctly
- Build under `ncb` → module-prefixed numbering + 4-column tables still correct

### Phase 3 Acceptance (Capture)
- Record 3-screen flow → `session.json` validates pydantic; events have document-coordinate bboxes; password redacted; result step after navigation; crop PNGs present; annotation boxes pixel-aligned on 125%-scaled Windows display; new-tab keeps recording.

### Phase 2 Acceptance (Providers)
- API mode: zero Tkinter popups
- Browser mode: exactly 1 paste per session
- 20-field screen: no truncation (max_tokens=8000)
- Killed field in fake LLM response: id-merge test shows no misalignment
